
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gipddecode` baraye tabdil dadan file-haye format GIPD (Google IP Discovery) be format-haye ghabl-e khandan estefade mishavad. In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad etela'ati ra ke az Google darbareye IP address-ha gerefte-id, analiz konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `-i <input_file>`  --> 📥 File-e voroodi GIPD ra moshakhas mikonad.
    🔹 `-o <output_file>` --> 📤 File-e khorooji ke etela'at tabdil shode dar aan zakhire mishavad ra moshakhas mikonad.
    🔹 `-f <output_format>` --> ⚙️ Format-e khorooji ra moshakhas mikonad (masalan, JSON ya CSV). Agar moshakhas nashavad, format pishfarz estefade mishavad.
    🔹 `-v`              --> 📢 Namayesh etela'at bishtar dar mored amal kard-e dastoor (verbose mode).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gipddecode -i input.gipd -o output.json -f json

    🔹 File `input.gipd` ra be format JSON tabdil mikonad va dar file `output.json` zakhire mikonad.

    $ gipddecode -i data.gipd -o result.txt

    🔹 File `data.gipd` ra be format pishfarz tabdil mikonad va dar file `result.txt` zakhire mikonad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gipddecode -i google_ips.gipd -o ips.txt

    🔹  File `google_ips.gipd` ke shamel etela'at IP address-haye Google ast, be file `ips.txt` tabdil mishavad ke ghabl-e khandan baraye analiz ast.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gipddecode` command is used to convert GIPD (Google IP Discovery) format files into a more readable format. It helps you analyze information obtained from Google about IP addresses.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `-i <input_file>`  --> 📥 Specifies the input GIPD file.
    🔹 `-o <output_file>` --> 📤 Specifies the output file where the converted data will be saved.
    🔹 `-f <output_format>` --> ⚙️ Specifies the output format (e.g., JSON or CSV). If not specified, a default format is used.
    🔹 `-v`              --> 📢 Displays more information about the command's operation (verbose mode).

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gipddecode -i input.gipd -o output.json -f json

    🔹 Converts the `input.gipd` file to JSON format and saves it in the `output.json` file.

    $ gipddecode -i data.gipd -o result.txt

    🔹 Converts the `data.gipd` file to the default format and saves it in the `result.txt` file.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gipddecode -i google_ips.gipd -o ips.txt

    🔹 Converts the `google_ips.gipd` file, which contains Google IP address information, into the `ips.txt` file, making it readable for analysis.
